  <attachment id="law">
    <section>
      <num>1.1</num>
      <heading>Short Title</heading>
      <text><cite path="attachments|law">This enactment</cite> shall be known as the "The Right of Kiowa Voters to Vote by Mail Act of 2022" ("Act").</text>
    </section>
    <section>
      <num>1.2</num>
      <heading>Purpose</heading>
      <text>The purpose of <cite path="attachments|law">this Act</cite> is to authorize the Kiowa Election Commission to mail out ballots in all elections to all adult members of the Kiowa Tribe who maintain a current address to the Tribe, notwithstanding any law, ordinance, or resolution of the Tribe to the contrary and/or previously enacted by the Tribe.</text>
    </section>
    <section>
      <num>1.3</num>
      <heading>Findings</heading>
      <para>
        <num>(a)</num>
        <text>Right of all adult Kiowa Tribal Members to vote is a fundamental component of democracy.</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(b)</num>
        <text>Fair and impartial elections are critical to guarantee the peoples right to choose their representation and to be governed by them.</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(c)</num>
        <text>In response to a recent BIA/CFR Court Order, the Legislature finds the need to solidify and guarantee the right of all Kiowa Tribal voters to receive a ballot by mail to all elections.</text>
      </para>
    </section>
    <section>
      <num>1.4</num>
      <heading>Authorization</heading>
      <para>
        <num>(a)</num>
        <text>The Legislature hereby authorizes and directs the Kiowa Tribe Election Commission to mail out ballots to all adult members of the Kiowa Tribe who maintain a current address with the Tribe in all elections, notwithstanding any law, ordinance, or resolution of the Tribe to the contrary and/or previously enacted by the Tribe.</text>
      </para>
    </section>
